                    <span>This IS the bible to limit hold'em....a must have.</span>
                  
                    <div class="CustomerReviewSummary">This book is not for no-limit holdem!</div>
                    <div>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Rating: </span>
                      <span>3</span>
                      <span class="ItemCaption">Helpful: </span>
                      <span>17</span>
                      /
                      <span>20</span>
                      votes <span class="ItemCaption">Reviewed: </span>
                      <span>2004-10-26</span>
                    </div>
                    <span>I don't know if other reviews touch on this, but this book is intended for limit holdem games.  While many of the ideas can be applied to no limit games, the author continually discusses limit play.  This is important since there is little in the book about pot odds and implied odds.  And since the author assumes you are playing limit games, the discussion regarding these topics is limited to "if you are raised on your right" and so on.  For people who want specifics about how much of a raise on your right should cause you to fold, this book is lacking.
<br />
<br />I will say, however, that the section on hand rankings has improved my play (in both limit and no limit games).  But if you are looking for a specific no limit book, you might try something else.</span>
                  
              
